tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE QuantumExperiments (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name TEXT,
  experiment_date DATE,
  researcher_name TEXT,
  research_institution TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE experiments (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  experiment_date DATE,
  researcher_id INT,
  location VARCHAR(100),
  CONSTRAINT fk_researcher FOREIGN KEY (researcher_id)
    REFERENCES researchers (researcher_id)
);

CREATE TABLE results (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  result_data JSON,
  CONSTRAINT fk_experiment FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id)
    REFERENCES experiments (experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE devices (
  device_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  device_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  device_type VARCHAR(50),
  experiment_id INT,
  CONSTRAINT fk_experiment FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id)
    REFERENCES experiments (experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_experiments (
	experiment_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	experiment_name VARCHAR(100),
	experiment_date TIMESTAMP,
	experiment_description TEXT,
	is_successful BOOLEAN
)

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
	result_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	experiment_id INT,
	result_value DECIMAL,
	result_date TIMESTAMP,
	FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES quantum_experiments(experiment_id)
)

CREATE TABLE researchers (
	researcher_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	researcher_name VARCHAR(100),
	researcher_email VARCHAR(100),
	researcher_institution VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE equipment (
	equipment_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	equipment_name VARCHAR(100),
	equipment_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE research_teams (
	team_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	team_name VARCHAR(100),
	team_leader_id INT,
	FOREIGN KEY (team_leader_id) REFERENCES researchers(researcher_id)
)
